1.0.0.name: wordpress/blunt-ga
1.0.0.description:
Important Notice: This plugin uses "ga.js" and not the new version of GA "analytics.js" currently in public beta. If your GA account is set up for the new version then you cannot use this plugin. I have added making this plugin compatable with the new version of Google Analytics to my "To-Do" list.

This plugin installs Google Analytics (GA). It can be used to set up event tracking of document, file, email, click to call and outbound links. Form submission event tracking can be set up. Event tracking can be added to all conversion pages. Cross Site tracking and linking can also be set up. Tracking can be set up to track clicks as either events or as virtual page views.

The main features and advantages of this plugin are:

  • All events can be managed and viewed seperately in Google Analytics
  • All events can be sent as virtual page views
  • Outbo
